UMUAHIA – The mini-grid solar energy that will provide electricity to the Bende Federal Constit­uency of Abia State nonstop for 25 years is to be built in Bende town by the federal government in the new year. This is coming as the reha­bilitation and reconstruction of the Umuahia-Bende-Oha­fia federal road estimated at N12billion and awarded to a construction company will commence in earnest in 2021. Hon. Benjamin Okezie Kalu, a federal lawmaker, who dropped this hint during a town hall meeting at Bende on Wednesday, explained that the Umuahia-Bende-Ohafia road currently being rehabilitated by Federal Roads Mainte­nance Agency (FERMA) will be comprehensively expand­ed and dualised from 2021. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION